            <span class="utterance" who="serrasE" start="632.770" end="x">Experiments. And which people were to go into the gas[Footnote 2: The Yiddish word 'gass' means 'street, outdoors, 'German 'gasse'. The expression gehn in gass, means 'to go out, to go for a walk, etc. But in the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lagers</a> it coincided with 'going to the gas chambers, assignment to gas-killing. Since the word gas for volatiles is homophonic with gass for street, the interviewer was prone to confuse the two, more so that he could not help often fail to perceive correctly the meaning of the expression 'ghen in gas', as 'gas-killing'. —D.P.B.].</span>
