            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Edith Serras</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="serrasE" start="1021.173" end="x">. . . from our blood. Leaving the work, we would take the bodies [?] on our shoulders and carry them to the crematories. The <a class="term" href="#vothG_ss">SS</a> men beat us [demanding] that we have respect[??; may also mean, That we take care of] for the dead bodies—we should carry them well [properly]. But we, ourselves, were so weak; we, ourselves, could not walk on our feet from such a day's work on a half a liter of soup . . . of water.</span>
