            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="serrasE" start="x" end="x">Yes. When they were hanged they stepped up [to the scaffold] with shouts and stamping feet . . . [triumphantly]</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="x" end="x">The girls?</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Edith Serras</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="serrasE" start="x" end="x">They were going not like to their death, but they were going like six heroes, laughingly. And they jumped on the table and they shouted 'Vengeance!'</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="x" end="x">[In English] This concludes Spool Number 35, which is oversize—thirty-eight minutes long. A spool by Mrs. Serras, Edith Serras, who lives now in <a class="placename" href="#vothL13">Paris</a>. She was a French deportee.</span>
        </li>
